# NPM API Essentials

This package contains essentials functionality for node API:s.

## Releases

This package follows `semantic-release` versioning, based on commit messages. Release rules are configured in [.releaserc.json](/.releaserc.json), and follow the pattern:

| Commit message                                   | Release type                  |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------- |
| `fix: fix dependency issue`                      | Patch Release                 |
| `feat: add 'width' option`                       | Minor Release                 |
| `breaking: The 'width' option has been removed.` | Major/Breaking Release <br /> |

Whenever a push is made to main containing one or more of the above commit patterns, a new release will be created automatically. If you _don't_ want to trigger a new release, prefix the commit message with something else, such as `ci: fix broken pipeline`, `docs: update docs` etc.

